# UNO Real Game Engine Module
#
# IMPORTANT ARCHITECTURAL RULE:
# All future UNO rules (such as draw card rules, matching card colors/numbers, special card behaviors
# like wild/skip/reverse, turn order management, direction of play, and victory conditions) 
# MUST be implemented inside this 'game' engine module.
#
# NEVER implement gameplay logic directly inside socket handlers in index.ts or other transport layer files.
# The socket layer should only act as a thin network transport wrapper that forwards user actions to the
# game engine and broadcasts the resulting engine state changes.
